      "rationale": "The FEA ensemble employed Ansys Mechanical 2022 R2 under an institutionally managed license. Software qualification records, version control logs, and regression test suites were reviewed and found compliant with the required SQA gradation for a Model Risk Level 3 assessment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems with known analytical solutions verified; residual norms reported below solver tolerance.",
      "rationale": "Patch tests and simple beam bending benchmarks with closed-form solutions were executed. All residuals converged below 1e-6; results matched analytical solutions within 0.3%, satisfying Gradation 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study performed; discretization error estimated via Richardson extrapolation and shown to be <2% for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the screw-rod construct. Richardson extrapolation yielded discretization uncertainty estimates of 0.8–1.4% for stiffness and yield force QoIs, exceeding the Gradation 2 threshold and reaching Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver convergence confirmed; energy balance checked across all load steps.",
      "rationale": "Newton-Raphson iterations converged within 8 substeps for all load cases. Energy balance errors remained below 0.05% across the full 40 mm displacement sweep, consistent with Gradation 2 requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Modeling assumptions documented; independent peer review of boundary conditions and material assignments completed.",
      "rationale": "An independent analyst reviewed all boundary condition assignments, contact definitions, and material property inputs against the documented modeling protocol. No discrepancies were identified. Use-error risk assessed as low."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum mechanics framework appropriate for titanium alloy screw-rod construct; contact formulation validated against F1717 geometry.",
      "rationale": "Linear-elastic continuum mechanics with nonlinear contact (augmented Lagrangian) was selected. The model form is consistent with prior FDA-published FEA guidance for metallic spinal implants and is appropriate for the elastic-to-yield regime captured in the F1717 protocol."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from coupon testing of same lot material; geometric dimensions from CMM measurements of test articles.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V material properties (E, yield stress, Poisson ratio) were derived from tensile coupon tests on material from the same manufacturing lot as the test constructs. Geometry was extracted from CMM data with <0.02 mm dimensional uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥5 constructs per laboratory; sample traceability to manufacturing lot documented.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were tested across two independent laboratories (6 + 5). All constructs were traceable to a single manufacturing lot. Inter-laboratory variability in stiffness was 4.2%, within acceptable bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Multiple load configurations or environmental conditions tested to span the COU space; temperature and humidity controlled and recorded.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 configuration (compression-bending at ambient conditions). Only one load ratio was evaluated, limiting coverage of the COU space. Achieved level is below required; this known gap is acknowledged in the overall credibility argument."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model inputs confirmed to match experimental specimen parameters within measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team confirmed that material property values and geometric parameters used in the simulation were consistent with the test article characterization data. Equivalency between experimental and simulation inputs was reviewed and accepted as part of the overall credibility evaluation process."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (E/uval) computed for all QoIs; E/uval < 1.96 for acceptance.",
      "rationale": "E/uval was computed for stiffness (0.84), yield force (1.12), and force at 40 mm (0.97). All values fell below the 1.96 threshold. QoI differences ranged from 2.1% to 7.8%, within the <10% acceptance bound. Gradation 3 output comparison achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes; stiffness and yield force are regulatory-relevant endpoints per FDA guidance.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the primary endpoints specified in ASTM F1717 and cited in FDA 510(k) guidance for spinal implant systems. These QoIs directly correspond to the clinical risk of mechanical failure leading to revision surgery."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments replicate the F1717 protocol geometry, loading, and material system used in the COU; no extrapolation beyond validated domain.",
      "rationale": "The validation activity directly mirrors the COU: identical screw geometry (7.5 mm non-cannulated), identical loading protocol (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending), and identical material system (Ti-6Al-4V). No extrapolation beyond the validated parameter space is required for the intended regulatory submission."
    }
  ],
